 25	 *   - `small-interface-deep-implementation`: `load`, `editDocument`,
 26	 *     `applyImageUpload`, `publish` hide the whole draft/published key-pair
 27	 *     choreography, the double draft-read, and the merge/decode/re-encode dance.
 28	 *   - `make-impossible-states-unrepresentable`: every operation is addressed by
 29	 *     a `ContentScope`, a *closed* union that routes through `scopeKeys` to a
 30	 *     real `{ draftKey, publishedKey }` pair. An editor cannot target a key that
 31	 *     is not a known scope — the bucket-key constants stop leaking to the route.
 32	 *   - `boundary-discipline`: decode happens here, once, before a draft is
 33	 *     stored; a rejected edit fails with an `IssueError` carrying the dotted
 34	 *     field issues the editor surfaces.
 35	 *
 36	 * `ContentScope` is a single-inhabitant union *today* (`{ kind: 'site' }`). The
 37	 * scope dimension is real — it carries the draft/published key PAIR plus the
 38	 * reconciliation — so Branch 5 *widens the union* (page/form scopes) rather than
 39	 * retrofitting a parameter: `scopeKeys` already has one case now and N cases
 40	 * later, and `load`/`editDocument`/`publish` all route through it.
 41	 */
