518	    // immediately, with no redeploy and without waiting out the TTL (D3). This
519	    // is the built-in cache's `invalidate`: it expires the cached document and
520	    // clears the stored result, so the next `getSiteContent` recomputes
521	    // `fetchDocument`. (`make-operations-idempotent`: busting an already-empty
522	    // or already-expired cache is a harmless no-op.) The built-in does NOT
523	    // pre-empt an in-flight refresh: a publish landing during one is masked
524	    // because that refresh re-arms the TTL with its pre-publish document, so
525	    // the stale window measured from the publish is `(the refresh's remaining
526	    // bucket-read duration) + one TTL`, not ≤ one TTL. That documented window
527	    // is within D3's "visible on the next read after the window" contract
528	    // (see the `Content` doc above for the full mechanism).
529	    const bust = Effect.fn('Content.bust')(function* () {
530	      yield* invalidate;
